{title: Holy, Holy, Holy!}
{subtitle: Lord God Almighty}
{key: Eb}
{time: 4/4}
{tempo: 88}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[Eb]Holy, holy, [Bb]holy! [Eb]Lord God Al[Ab]mighty!
[Eb]Early in the [Bb]morning our [Eb]song shall rise to [Bb]Thee;
[Eb]Holy, holy, [Bb]holy! [Eb]Merciful and [Ab]Mighty!
[Eb]God in three [Bb]Persons, [Ab]blessed [Eb]Trinity!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
[Eb]Holy, holy, [Bb]holy! [Eb]All the saints a[Ab]dore Thee,
[Eb]Casting down their [Bb]golden crowns a[Eb]round the glassy [Bb]sea;
[Eb]Cherubim and [Bb]seraphim [Eb]falling down be[Ab]fore Thee,
[Eb]Who wert, and [Bb]art, and [Ab]ever[mo]re shalt [Eb]be.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
[Eb]Holy, holy, [Bb]holy! [Eb]Though the darkness [Ab]hide Thee,
[Eb]Though the eye of [Bb]sinful man Thy [Eb]glory may not [Bb]see;
[Eb]Only Thou art [Bb]holy; [Eb]there is none be[Ab]side Thee,
[Eb]Perfect in [Bb]power, in [Ab]love, and [Eb]purity.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
[Eb]Holy, holy, [Bb]holy! [Eb]Lord God Al[Ab]mighty!
[Eb]All Thy works shall [Bb]praise Thy name, in [Eb]earth, and sky, and [Bb]sea;
[Eb]Holy, holy, [Bb]holy! [Eb]Merciful and [Ab]Mighty!
[Eb]God in three [Bb]Persons, [Ab]blessed [Eb]Trinity!
{end_of_verse}
